OL,6,FAsked if she would receive to
OL,7,Fministerial severance pay, the Prime
OL,8,FMinister's official spokesman referred
OL,9,Fto legal rules stating that ministers
OL,10,Funder the age of 65 are entitled to a
OL,11,Floss-of-office payment worth a quarter
OL,12,Fof their annual ministerial salary if
OL,13,Fthey are not appointed to a new role
OL,14,Fwithin three weeks.
OL,16,FAsked if Sir Keir Starmer would
OL,17,Fencourage Ms Haigh to voluntarily
OL,18,Fforego the payment, the spokesman
OL,19,Fsaid: "He'd leave that up to her."
